      "content": "I hear how draining and frustrating that feeling of being stuck in a repetitive cycle is. It sounds like you're carrying a lot of exhaustion right now, especially when you feel like your efforts don't lead to lasting change. It's completely understandable to feel like you're wired to fail when life keeps knocking you back down after you think you've finally found stability.\n\nSometimes, the most important step isn't trying to \"fix\" the cycle itself, but acknowledging that the exhaustion is real and that your feelings of hopelessness are valid. You don't have to solve everything today, but if you're open to it, talking to a therapist or a trusted support person could help you untangle some of these patterns without having to do it alone. You're not alone in this, and there are people who can help you navigate through the fatigue.",
